examples.en: He lived in obedience to the church's teachings.
She peered into one of the church's murky chapels.
He believed in the church's message of forgiveness.
It's not the church's job to interfere in politics.
The events pose a challenge to the church's leadership.
The bishop outlined the church's views in a pastoral letter.
This belief was irreconcilable with the Church's doctrine of salvation.
The church's blackened ceiling is the result of centuries of candle smoke.
...the old church's crypt is the final resting place for the president and his beloved wife...
During the vigil service the church's Gothic interior was illumed by the light of hundreds of tapers.
